semen: the living gods of Haiti", "work_id": 94619, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 899821, "title": "[Maya Deren Compilation]", "work_id": 80675, "role": "co-director", "role_id": 959, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 754568, "title": "A Study in choreography for camera", "work_id": 73326, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 855202, "title": "Meditation on violence", "work_id": 70266, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1917-05-12", "date_of_death": "1961-10-13", "genders": [{"id": 5, "name": "Female", "slug": "female"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 1, "name": "United States of America", "slug": "united-states-of-america"}], "biography": "Maya Deren (born Eleonora Derenkowska, Ukrainian: Елеоно́ра Деренко́вська; April 29, 1917 – October 13, 1961) was a Ukrainian-born American experimental filmmaker and important promoter of the avant-garde in the 1940s and 1950s. Deren was also a choreographer, dancer, film theorist, poet, lecturer, writer, and photographer.\nThe function of film, Deren believed, was to create an experience. She combined her expertise in dance and choreography, ethnography, the African spirit religion of Haitian Vodou,  symbolist poetry and gestalt psychology (student of Kurt Koffka)  in a series of perceptual, black-and-white short films. Using editing, multiple exposures, jump-cutting, superimposition, slow-motion, and other camera techniques to her advantage, Deren abandoned established notions of physical space and time, in carefully planned films with specific conceptual aims.Meshes of the Afternoon (1943), her collaboration with Alexander Hammid, has been one of the most influential experimental films in American cinema history. She went on to make several films of her own, including At Land (1944), A Study in Choreography for Camera (1945), and Ritual in Transfigured Time (1946), writing, producing, directing, editing, and photographing them with help from only one other person, Hella Heyman, her camerawoman.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T12:26:46.564289+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2687, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maya_Deren"}], "uuid": "8d2a354c-fa0f-4f5b-a748-ac5ec438e29a", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "24893", "external_references": [{"id": 11467, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q450382"}, {"id": 11468, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "59193774"}, {"id": 11469, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n83179417"}, {"id": 11470, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n83179417"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:31:21.637776+10:00"}, {"id": 12693, "name": "John B Murray", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 861129, "title": "Yoga and the individual", "work_id": 74993, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1985143, "title": "Libido", "work_id": 81035, "role": "co-director", "role_id": 959, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2266659, "title": "We of the never never [DVD]", "work_id": 95621, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 898342, "title": "A Personal history of the Australian surf: being the confessions of a straight poofter", "work_id": 78369, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2677710, "title": "Assistance India : people to people", "work_id": 65020, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1804326, "title": "Lonely Hearts", "work_id": 80773, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 808728, "title": "The Plight of Tibet and the Dalai Lama: interviews with Tibetian refugees", "work_id": 91560, "role": "producer/director", "role_id": 31, "is_primary